Patient: What can I do to manage my fluid intake?

Healthcare Educator: Try to reduce your salt intake. This can help control fluid in your body.

Patient: But my traditional meals are high in salt. How can I change this?

Healthcare Educator: You could try using herbs and spices for flavor instead of salt.

Patient: It's hard for me to exercise due to my neighborhood. What can I do?

Healthcare Educator: You could try indoor exercises or consider joining a local gym if possible.

Patient: Why is reducing salt intake and exercise important for heart failure?

Healthcare Educator: They help manage fluid levels and keep your heart healthy.